  <section>
    <div class="container">
      <div class="page-wrapper">
        <p class="lead">Planning a sports banquet is a lot like coaching a season — you need a game plan, a timeline, and a team that executes. Here's exactly what to do in each of the 8 weeks leading up to your big night.</p>

        <h2>Week 8 — Set the Foundation</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Pick a date</strong> — Check the school calendar, avoid exam weeks, holidays, and other major events</li>
          <li><strong>Choose venue</strong> — School cafeteria? Local banquet hall? Restaurant? Church basement? Book now.</li>
          <li><strong>Form committee</strong> — Coach + booster club rep + 2-3 parent volunteers</li>
          <li><strong>Set budget</strong> — Typical range: $15-35 per person including food, decorations, and awards</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Week 7 — Plan the Program</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Determine menu</strong> — Buffet vs plated? Caterer or potluck? Check dietary restrictions</li>
          <li><strong>Send save-the-date</strong> — Email to parents and athletes, post on team social media</li>
          <li><strong>Order awards</strong> — Trophies, medals, plaques typically take 2-3 weeks to produce</li>
          <li><strong>Choose decor theme</strong> — Team colors, sport-specific decorations, table arrangements</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Week 5-6 — Order & Organize</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Order centerpieces</strong> — Custom 3D printed centerpieces need time for production and shipping. Order at least 3 weeks before the banquet.</li>
          <li><strong>Send formal invitations</strong> — Include RSVP deadline (2 weeks before event)</li>
          <li><strong>Confirm venue details</strong> — Setup time, audiovisual equipment, seating capacity</li>
          <li><strong>Collect RSVPs</strong> — Track headcount for food ordering</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Week 3-4 — Finalize Details</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Confirm final headcount</strong> — Give final numbers to caterer/venue</li>
          <li><strong>Finalize award categories</strong> — Decide who presents each award</li>
          <li><strong>Prepare slide show or video</strong> — Season photos, highlight reel, senior memories</li>
          <li><strong>Assign volunteers</strong> — Setup crew, registration table, cleanup team</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Week 2 — Prepare & Rehearse</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Create program/running order</strong> — Dinner, welcome, coach speech, awards, senior recognition, closing</li>
          <li><strong>Prepare speeches</strong> — Coach writes remarks, assign speaker order</li>
          <li><strong>Print materials</strong> — Programs, name tags, table signs, place cards</li>
          <li><strong>Confirm vendor deliveries</strong> — Centerpieces, flowers, cake, AV equipment</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Week 1 — Last Week</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Confirm all orders</strong> — Call every vendor to confirm delivery times</li>
          <li><strong>Pack emergency kit</strong> — Safety pins, tape, marker, extra tablecloths, stapler</li>
          <li><strong>Email reminder to guests</strong> — Time, location, what to bring</li>
          <li><strong>Walk through the venue</strong> — Know where everything goes</li>
        </ul>

        <h2>Day Of — Execute</h2>
        <ul>
          <li><strong>Arrive 2 hours early</strong> — Setup tables, test AV, arrange centerpieces</li>
          <li><strong>Check-in table</strong> — Greet guests, hand out programs</li>
          <li><strong>Designate a timer</strong> — Someone to keep the ceremony moving</li>
          <li><strong>Take photos</strong> — Team photo, award photos, candid moments</li>
          <li><strong>Cleanup plan</strong> — Assign 4-5 volunteers for teardown</li>
        </ul>

